📊 Core Formulas & Logic

🧮 Cladding Area

  • Walls = (Length x Height x 2) + (Width x Height x 2)

  • Roof = (Roof Width x Length) x 2 for apex / mono pitch

  • Add % for wastage (e.g. +10%)

🔩 Fixings

  • Example: 8 fixings per m² (adjustable)

  • Fixings = Total cladding area × fixings per m²

📏 Flashings

  • Ridge flashing = Building width / flashing length (rounded up)

  • Eaves = Lengths of both eaves / flashing length

  • Verge = Height of gable × 2 / flashing length

  • Each with 2–4 fixings per length

🌧️ Guttering

  • Gutter = Eave length

  • Brackets = One every 0.6 m

  • Downpipes = 1 per 10–12 m

  • Clips, outlets, joints auto-calculated

🔧 Behind the Scenes: What Roof Pitch Drives

If we use degrees, we’ll convert to radians for formulas, or use:

Rise=(Width/2)×tan(θ)Slope=(Width/2)/cos(θ)Rise = (Width / 2) × tan(θ) Slope = (Width / 2) / cos(θ) Rise=(Width/2)×tan(θ)Slope=(Width/2)/cos(θ)

This gives us:

  • Ridge Height = Eaves Height + Rise

  • Slope Length = √(Rise² + (Width/2)²)

  • Roof Area = Slope Length × Length × 2

🔍 Sheet 2: Calculations

Paste this below or on a second tab:

OutputFormula (in Excel)
Ridge Height=Eaves_Height + (Width/2) * TAN(RADIANS(Roof_Pitch))
Roof Slope Length (1 side)=SQRT((Width/2)^2 + (Ridge_Height - Eaves_Height)^2)
Total Roof Area (both sides)=Roof_Slope_Length * Length * 2
Wall Area=2*(Length + Width)*Eaves_Height
Gable Area (approx.)=Width * (Ridge_Height - Eaves_Height)
Sheet Count (Roof)=Roof_Area / Sheet_Coverage (Assume 1.0 m² per sheet or adjust as needed)
Fixings (Roof)=Roof_Area * 6 (adjust fixing density)
Flashings Needed=IF(Roof_Cladding_Type = "Box Profile", "Ridge, Barge, Eaves Flashing", "Custom")

🛠 Option 1: Custom HTML + JavaScript Web Form

You can host this yourself or use a service like GitHub Pages (free). Below is a basic template:

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Building Materials Calculator</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial; max-width: 600px; margin: auto; }
    label { display: block; margin-top: 1em; }
    input, select { width: 100%; padding: 8px; margin-top: 4px; }
    .output { margin-top: 1em; background: #f7f7f7; padding: 1em; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Materials Calculator</h1>
  <label>Length (m):<input type="number" id="length" value="25"></label>
  <label>Width (m):<input type="number" id="width" value="12"></label>
  <label>Eaves Height (m):<input type="number" id="height" value="4"></label>
  <label>Roof Pitch (°):
    <select id="pitch">
      <option>5</option><option>7.5</option><option>10</option>
      <option>12.5</option><option>15</option><option>22.5</option>
    </select>
  </label>

  <button onclick="calculate()">Calculate</button>

  <div class="output" id="result"></div>

  <script>
    function calculate() {
      const L = parseFloat(document.getElementById('length').value);
      const W = parseFloat(document.getElementById('width').value);
      const H = parseFloat(document.getElementById('height').value);
      const pitch = parseFloat(document.getElementById('pitch').value);
      const rise = (W/2)*Math.tan(pitch*Math.PI/180);
      const ridge = H + rise;
      const slope = Math.sqrt((W/2)**2 + rise**2);
      const roofArea = slope * L * 2;
      const wallArea = 2*(L + W)*H;

      document.getElementById('result').innerHTML = `
        <strong>Ridge Height:</strong> ${ridge.toFixed(2)} m<br>
        <strong>Roof Slope:</strong> ${slope.toFixed(2)} m<br>
        <strong>Roof Area:</strong> ${roofArea.toFixed(2)} m²<br>
        <strong>Wall Area:</strong> ${wallArea.toFixed(2)} m²
      `;
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>

You can:

  1. Copy & paste this into a file named index.html.

  2. Upload it to GitHub Pages, Netlify, or your own server.

  3. Test it in your browser or phone — all calculations run live.

  <script>
    function calculate() {
      const L = parseFloat(document.getElementById('length').value), 
            W = parseFloat(document.getElementById('width').value), 
            H = parseFloat(document.getElementById('height').value), 
            p = parseFloat(document.getElementById('pitch').value);
      const rise = (W/2)*Math.tan(p * Math.PI / 180),
            ridge = H + rise,
            slope = Math.sqrt((W/2)**2 + rise**2),
            roofArea = (slope * L * 2).toFixed(2),
            wallArea = (2 * (L + W) * H).toFixed(2);
      document.getElementById('result').innerHTML = `
        <strong>Ridge Height:</strong> ${ridge.toFixed(2)} m<br>
        <strong>Roof Slope:</strong> ${slope.toFixed(2)} m<br>
        <strong>Roof Area:</strong> ${roofArea} m²<br>
        <strong>Wall Area:</strong> ${wallArea} m²`;
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
